we learned about the local scope , global scope , LEGB 

Global variable: this is a variable that is defined outside any function and can be accessed anywhere in the code 

enclosing scope: this is the scope where its found outside the inner function unless the inner function has a local scope 

Built-in scope this is part of the basic version of python 

local scope: this is the area inside the function '


def greet(name): #name is local 
    message = f"Hello, {name}!"  # message is also in local 
    print(message)  # Accessing the local variable


